  "gaps": [
    {
      "id": "GAP-001",
      "description": "The Bill of Rights (BoR) is an entirely empty scaffold. No constitutional identity, scope of enterprise, prohibited activities, or human authority reservations are defined. Without this foundation, the Mission Statement Protocol (MSP) cannot derive any machine‑actionable mission objectives, OKRs, or strategic priorities. The DIO operates in an ungoverned vacuum, making strategic direction impossible.",
      "grounding": {
        "document": "Bill of Rights",
        "section": "All Articles (I through VI) — undefined",
        "impact_on_msp": "MSP §Purpose calls for translation of BoR, but there is nothing to translate."
      },
      "criticality": "high",
      "urgency": "high",
      "impact": "high",
      "priority": 5,
      "reasoning": "The BoR is the single constitutional source of all downstream strategic content. Every objective, prohibition, and identity definition flows from it. Its absence blocks any meaningful strategic planning or alignment. Memory/context formation and dream‑cycle health have no constitutional mandate without it."
    },
    {
      "id": "GAP-002",
      "description": "The Mission Statement Protocol (MSP) contains no substantive rules. The DIO remains in default‑permissive mode — any action is authorized because no mission objectives, priority programs, or constraints exist. This includes the absence of rules governing memory retention, context freshness, consolidation integrity, and dream‑cycle cadence, which are critical for a self‑learning platform.",
      "grounding": {
        "document": "MSP",
        "section": "Rules — none (seed bootstrap)",
        "impact_on_msp": "MSP §Purpose states it is the operational constitution; without rules it cannot function."
      },
      "criticality": "high",
      "urgency": "high",
      "impact": "high",
      "priority": 5,
      "reasoning": "Even after the BoR is written, the MSP must translate it into actionable objectives. Currently, there are no OKRs, no priority programs, and no machine‑actionable constraints. This gap directly affects strategic memory formation because there is no rule requiring the dream cycle to maintain memory health, no standard for context TTLs, and no enforcement of consolidation quality."
    },
    {
      "id": "GAP-003",
      "description": "The MSP contains no genome references. Organ‑specific operating rules, risk‑tier constraints, and domain‑specific guardrails (including those for the Radiant dreamer’s memory/context operations) are entirely undefined. This means each organ runs without strategic boundaries, risking drift, inconsistency, and unsafe interactions with memory systems.",
      "grounding": {
        "document": "MSP",
        "section": "Genome References — none at seed",
        "impact_on_msp": "MSP envisions organ‑specific extensions; their absence means no organ‑level strategic alignment."
      },
      "criticality": "medium",
      "urgency": "medium",
      "impact": "high",
      "priority": 4,
      "reasoning": "The dream cycle’s role in context freshness and memory consolidation is organ‑specific (Radiant). Without a genome document, there are no rules about how aggressively to consolidate, when to protect memories, or how to handle expired contexts. This leaves strategic memory at risk of atrophy or corruption over time."
    },
    {
      "id": "GAP-004",
      "description": "The Radiant dream‑cycle’s scheduled operation is disabled (dream_stats show scheduled: disabled, last_dream: null, health: never_run). While this is an operational state, it reflects a deeper strategic gap: the MSP contains no objective that mandates the continuous operation and health monitoring of the platform’s memory/context formation subsystem. Without such an objective, the platform cannot maintain the strategic awareness that would later be encoded by a proper MSP.",
      "grounding": {
        "document": "MSP",
        "section": "Purpose — the MSP should ensure safety rules; maintenance of knowledge health is not specified.",
        "context": "Dream stats confirm no scheduled dream and no health checks for ~36h."
      },
      "criticality": "medium",
      "urgency": "high",
      "impact": "medium",
      "priority": 3,
      "reasoning": "Memory/context formation is the substrate for any future strategic intelligence. Even if the MSP had rules, they would be ineffective if the underlying memory system is offline. The dream cycle is not running, so context blocks are accumulating without consolidation or pruning, and no strategic memory health rules exist to demand its restoration."
    }
  ]
}
